B.amh=new A.e("Diagram 4 shows the Yagura castle, Kin-Yagura to be exact, which is known to be sturdy when attacked from above. Diagram 5 is a variation in which the Silver is on 6g instead of 7g, where the Gold was in Diagram 4. You may find the two Golds, one on top of another along the 7th file, sufficiently tight. You might also notice that the Gold on 7h is doubly secured, i.e., by the Gold on 7g and the Silver on 6g. But there is a deadly defect here. Let me show you by means of how White plays from this position.")
B.M_=new A.q("l8/1r7/2np5/2pbp4/pp7/2PPP4/PPGS5/1KG6/LN7 w p","Diagram 5")
